headline: 2 Reasons to Like LRCX (and 1 Not So Much)
summary: Since July 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 97.8%. But one standout stock has doubled the market - over the past five years, Lam Research has surged 200% to $97.19 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 34.2% in the last six months thanks to its solid quarterly results, beating the S&P by 28.5%.
